title: HMNZS Hawea (2007)
text:
HMNZS "Hawea" is a <a href="Lake-class%20inshore%20patrol%20vessel">Lake-class inshore patrol vessel</a> of the <a href="Royal%20New%20Zealand%20Navy">Royal New Zealand Navy</a>. "Hawea" was constructed between 2004 and 2007, and commissioned on 1 May 2009. She performs border and fisheries protection patrols.
"Hawea" is the third ship of this name to serve in the Royal New Zealand Navy and is named after <a href="Lake%20H%C4%81wea">Lake Hāwea</a>.
